03:19.273 --> 03:21.973
Oh, no, don't tell me
Eileen's still doing

03:22.075 --> 03:23.909
her stupid Valueco ritual.

03:24.011 --> 03:27.212
Eileen: Damn right she is.
And let me tell you why.

03:27.314 --> 03:29.948
There's no crowds.
Everything's two-for-one.

03:30.050 --> 03:31.016
It's heaven.

03:31.118 --> 03:33.084
You should be spending tonight with him.

03:33.186 --> 03:34.219
Oh, it's okay.

03:34.321 --> 03:36.288
I respect her wishes
not to observe the holiday,

03:36.390 --> 03:40.125
unless you're reconsidering because Cupid
hit you with his little love arrow.

03:40.193 --> 03:42.894
I am not moved by a flying fat man-baby.

03:42.996 --> 03:45.563
Enjoy the rest of your
no-big-deal Tuesday.

03:52.053 --> 03:53.905
You are a Valentine's Day Scrooge.

03:54.007 --> 03:55.140
I am not.

03:55.242 --> 03:56.975
Clive's known about this
since the day after Christmas,

03:57.077 --> 03:59.477
when they started putting up
all the Valentine's stuff.

03:59.579 --> 04:01.913
You know that's how stores
try to monetize love.

04:02.015 --> 04:03.481
You know who else does that?

04:03.583 --> 04:04.549
Pimps.

04:04.651 --> 04:06.084
They're a lot less
in-your-face about it.

04:06.186 --> 04:07.285
Well, I enjoy the holiday,

04:07.387 --> 04:09.220
but I'm not doing
anything special, either.

04:09.256 --> 04:11.423
Why don't you stop by here
before Valueco?

04:11.525 --> 04:12.891
We're doing inventory tonight.

04:12.960 --> 04:14.825
Oh, perfect! I love inventory!

04:14.910 --> 04:16.144
Do I get a clipboard and a checklist

04:16.238 --> 04:17.796
and one of those little
clicker counters?

04:17.898 --> 04:19.130
We don't have one of those.

04:19.232 --> 04:21.232
Oh, okay. That's fine.
I have one at home.

04:21.301 --> 04:23.802
How am I the one who's single?

04:23.904 --> 04:24.903
[Sighs]

04:24.972 --> 04:27.973
Yes, I would like some tapa.

04:35.515 --> 04:38.350
Hey, just don't get
in your head tonight, okay?

04:38.452 --> 04:41.353
We're just regular dudes hanging out
on a regular Tuesday.

04:41.455 --> 04:42.984
But it's Valentine's.

04:43.093 --> 04:44.601
I had this entire day planned

04:44.687 --> 04:46.458
since the moment
Brett and I started dating.

04:46.560 --> 04:49.468
Who says it's Valentine's Day?
Some stupid calendar?

04:49.562 --> 04:51.830
It might offer
a daily inspirational quote,

04:51.932 --> 04:53.631
but it can't tell us what day it is.

04:53.734 --> 04:55.600
All right.

04:57.104 --> 04:59.537
[Ohio Players'
"Love Rollercoaster" playing]

05:02.442 --> 05:05.243
You know what? It's...
This is not a big deal.

05:05.312 --> 05:07.553
It's, uh...
It's just a bunch of balloons.

05:07.639 --> 05:10.849
Yeah. Just pretend
it's heart disease awareness.

05:10.917 --> 05:12.484
Brett's uncle has a bad heart.

05:12.586 --> 05:14.252
Now I'll never get to meet him.

05:14.321 --> 05:16.821
You know what,
it's all about your perspective.

05:16.890 --> 05:19.891
See, if you... if you turn it
upside-down, you get a butt.

05:19.960 --> 05:22.293
If you point it out, boobies!

05:22.362 --> 05:24.305
Brett's uncle has boobies.

05:24.383 --> 05:26.498
That's how they diagnosed
his heart disease.

05:26.566 --> 05:29.567
Come on, buddy.
Let's try and cheer up, okay?

05:29.636 --> 05:32.604
Let's not talk about Brett
anymore or his uncle's breasts.

05:32.706 --> 05:33.838
Okay.

05:33.907 --> 05:36.674
But Brett was my first real
relationship, and I messed it up.

05:36.743 --> 05:38.009
He told me he loved me
and then I told him I loved him

05:38.045 --> 05:39.611
and then I took it back
and then he dumped me

05:39.679 --> 05:41.646
- and now I'm single forever.
- That is not true.

05:41.748 --> 05:43.247
There are plenty of other fish
in the sea.

05:43.310 --> 05:45.150
Fish was Brett's favorite food.

05:45.218 --> 05:47.952
And his favorite
body of water was the sea.

05:48.021 --> 05:49.036
[Groans]

05:51.625 --> 05:53.224
He's totally gonna ruin this night.

05:53.327 --> 05:54.859
That balloon stuff
was some of my best work,

05:54.928 --> 05:56.127
so I-I don't know what else to do.

05:56.229 --> 05:58.430
I have waited 18 years for this.

05:58.498 --> 06:00.899
And this is supposed to be
the night that romance finds me.

06:01.001 --> 06:02.367
[Door opens]

06:02.469 --> 06:05.070
Here it comes.

06:05.105 --> 06:07.305
And there it goes.

06:07.407 --> 06:08.773
My dad's really good in bed.

06:08.842 --> 06:10.942
I know this because he had
three children with my mom.

06:11.011 --> 06:12.310
- She didn't even like him.
- Hey!

06:12.412 --> 06:13.345
What was that?

06:13.413 --> 06:16.047
What is happening?

06:16.083 --> 06:17.882
They're consoling him.

06:17.951 --> 06:21.286
Almost like they're attracted
to his sadness.

06:21.355 --> 06:23.688
Is she... Is she petting him?

06:23.757 --> 06:25.490
Yeah, and the other one's
giving him a treat.

06:25.592 --> 06:28.660
He's like a puppy in a park
attracting every woman in sight.

06:28.762 --> 06:30.195
[Chuckles]

06:32.165 --> 06:34.099
He's our puppy.

06:35.535 --> 06:38.169
Our sad, gay puppy.

06:42.142 --> 06:46.511
♪ The night we met,
I knew I needed you so ♪

06:46.580 --> 06:48.480
Happy Valentine's Day!

06:48.582 --> 06:49.781
This is not inventory.

06:49.883 --> 06:51.983
I knew it was the only way
to get you to come.

06:52.052 --> 06:52.884
Hmm.

06:52.986 --> 06:55.453
Let's see. One liar... check.

06:55.555 --> 06:58.523
Come on, ladies!
It's time to play Spin the Bottle!

06:58.592 --> 06:59.724
Oh, this is ridiculous.

06:59.793 --> 07:02.293
Just be glad it's not
Seven Minutes in the Closet.

07:02.362 --> 07:03.561
Try 17 years.

07:03.630 --> 07:04.763
Whoo!

07:04.831 --> 07:09.768
Oh, hey, somebody owes me a kiss!

07:09.836 --> 07:11.236
He knows he's gay, right?

07:11.271 --> 07:13.638
He's wearing a choker.
I think he's aware.

07:13.740 --> 07:16.241
Valentine's Day
is Steve's favorite holiday.

07:16.309 --> 07:17.976
I'm a 3 on the Kinsey scale.

07:18.078 --> 07:20.712
This is the one time a year
I get to mix it up.

07:20.781 --> 07:22.947
Watch out, Eileen. You might be next.

07:23.016 --> 07:25.150
I'd rather drink the tears
of all your prom dates.

07:25.252 --> 07:26.084
Ooh!

07:26.186 --> 07:28.520
Scrooge is alive and well.

07:28.622 --> 07:30.855
I happen to believe
in the spirit of this night.

07:30.957 --> 07:32.157
Also, my astrologist said

07:32.259 --> 07:34.926
that I'm going to collide
with a strong man in uniform.

07:35.028 --> 07:36.795
Is this the astrologist
you pay in cold cuts?

07:36.930 --> 07:37.595
[Scoffs]

07:37.664 --> 07:39.297
- Oh!
- Oh!

07:39.366 --> 07:40.832
- Hi.
- Hi.

07:40.901 --> 07:42.385
Um, I was dropping off a shipment,

07:42.487 --> 07:44.702
and I was wondering if there was someone
that could sign for it.

07:44.805 --> 07:47.138
- I can help you with that.
- Oh, great.

07:47.207 --> 07:48.339
- Oh!
- Oh!

07:48.442 --> 07:49.340
Oh!

07:49.409 --> 07:51.476
- Oh, my. So sorry.
- Oh.

07:51.545 --> 07:53.413
- Um...
- Oh.

07:53.538 --> 07:55.046
Oh, my God, I'm so sorry.

07:55.148 --> 07:56.247
You have just a little something...

08:00.387 --> 08:01.985
There you go.

08:02.344 --> 08:03.922
Perfect.

08:03.990 --> 08:06.124
Oh, come on.

08:06.226 --> 08:07.759
Then when Kenny came out to me,
I was like,

08:07.861 --> 08:10.361
"Hey, I love you
no matter who you love."

08:10.464 --> 08:12.330
I scooped him up in my big arms

08:12.432 --> 08:14.799
and hugged him
for what seemed like days.

08:14.901 --> 08:16.422
That is so sweet.

08:16.539 --> 08:18.670
I want to hug you. Can I hug you?

08:18.772 --> 08:20.872
If you feel like you need to.

08:24.010 --> 08:26.744
I lose everything.

08:26.847 --> 08:29.280
Oh, we didn't order this.

08:29.349 --> 08:31.916
Your gay brother's having a hard time,

08:32.018 --> 08:33.551
so it's on the house.

08:35.822 --> 08:38.296
And you said we wouldn't find
anyone to hook up with tonight.

08:38.374 --> 08:39.256
[Coughs]

08:39.359 --> 08:41.192
Look, you can't let
a break-up destroy you.

08:41.294 --> 08:43.982
If you had this Valentine's Day
planned, why not do it anyway?

08:44.063 --> 08:45.763
I know a girl who got left at the altar

08:45.865 --> 08:47.832
but still went
on her honeymoon to Jamaica.

08:50.937 --> 08:51.836
Was it you, Liz?

08:51.938 --> 08:53.605
Yeah, mon.

08:53.707 --> 08:54.939
How was the calamari?

08:55.008 --> 08:58.009
Do you think your brother's
hungry for anything else?

08:58.111 --> 09:00.044
Um, I saw you had a seafood tower,

09:00.146 --> 09:02.080
but he's also a surf-and-turf guy.

09:02.182 --> 09:04.082
So do you also have a meat tower?

09:04.184 --> 09:06.351
Sure do.

09:06.453 --> 09:09.721
There's a little jazz club
around the corner.

09:09.823 --> 09:13.825
Maybe the two of us could
sneak away and grab some tapas?

09:13.927 --> 09:14.926
[Laughter]

09:15.028 --> 09:17.128
Let me just go check on the little guy,

09:17.197 --> 09:18.963
and, uh, I'll be right back.

09:19.065 --> 09:22.934
♪

09:23.036 --> 09:25.536
Where is my little guy?

09:25.639 --> 09:27.939
Jimmy, where's Kenny?

09:28.041 --> 09:29.907
I don't know. I thought he was with you.

09:30.010 --> 09:32.243
We lost our gay puppy.

09:32.345 --> 09:33.444
We got a dog?

09:33.546 --> 09:35.146
No. You meant Kenny.

09:35.248 --> 09:36.180
Oh, Jimmy.

09:37.246 --> 09:39.863
Oh, sorry. I forgot my Valueco card.

09:39.933 --> 09:41.730
- I'll be right out of your hair.
- That's okay.

09:41.792 --> 09:44.388
We were just finishing up
some active listening.

09:44.466 --> 09:46.849
I hear you say it makes you
feel alone in the universe

09:46.927 --> 09:49.520
when we talk about astronomy,
but it's my favorite subject.

09:49.632 --> 09:52.566
And I hear you say astronomy
is your favorite subject,

09:52.635 --> 09:54.535
but black holes really scare me.

09:54.604 --> 09:55.569
I hear you.

09:55.638 --> 09:56.637
I hear you.

09:56.706 --> 09:58.739
As usual, I'm confused but not worried.

09:58.808 --> 10:00.313
So carry on.

10:00.407 --> 10:01.308
Mom, if you want to stick around

10:01.410 --> 10:03.244
for a little bit, we're about
to play The Game of Life.

10:03.312 --> 10:04.612
Yeah, it's more fun with three people.

10:04.680 --> 10:06.016
Are you sure you don't
want to exchange cards

10:06.079 --> 10:07.414
and serenade each other?

10:07.517 --> 10:09.150
No, Ethan has a shaky vibrato.

10:09.218 --> 10:10.451
I'd never let it happen.

10:10.520 --> 10:13.020
Well, you two are weird. But I'm in.

10:13.089 --> 10:14.889
Great. This is gonna be
so fun, Mrs. O'Neal.

10:14.991 --> 10:15.723
Ah!

10:15.825 --> 10:17.158
I'm always the red car.

10:19.162 --> 10:20.594
What's going on?

10:20.630 --> 10:22.630
Uh, have you seen Kenny?

10:22.698 --> 10:25.166
- Isn't he with you?
- Yes! Yes.

10:25.268 --> 10:27.835
Uh, but have you...
but have you seen him,

10:27.870 --> 10:29.948
you know, on, like, a deeper level?

10:30.049 --> 10:31.972
I just feel like we never
really look at each other.

10:32.074 --> 10:34.141
- Nope.
- Aah!

10:34.243 --> 10:35.843
And they're weird, too.

10:35.912 --> 10:37.652
I keep texting Kenny, and all I get back

10:37.723 --> 10:40.548
are these three dots that keep
disappearing. What is that?

10:40.650 --> 10:42.082
Well, that means he's typing
something and then erasing it.

10:42.118 --> 10:46.654
Or it could be he's tied up trying
to text us back using only his nose.

10:46.756 --> 10:48.689
What's going on? Where's Kenny?

10:48.791 --> 10:49.857
Um, we split up.

10:49.926 --> 10:52.159
We are doing a Valentine's Day
scavenger hunt.

10:52.228 --> 10:53.294
So, come on, Jimmy.

10:53.329 --> 10:55.629
Let's go find that spatula so we can go.

10:57.800 --> 10:59.466
Found the spatula!

10:59.535 --> 11:00.901
That's a ladle.

11:01.003 --> 11:04.238
- Dad.
- Fine. We lost him.

11:04.307 --> 11:05.873
Spatula.

11:06.008 --> 11:08.642
- Tongs, Jimmy.
- How could you lose him?

11:08.744 --> 11:10.277
Because we got distracted by women.

11:10.379 --> 11:12.346
And a seafood/meat tower.

11:12.448 --> 11:15.082
I have pork chop in my pocket.

11:15.184 --> 11:19.553
Shannon, you keep tabs on everyone.
Do you have any idea where he may be?

11:19.622 --> 11:21.856
I'd check his Instagram.
He can't keep off of it.

11:21.924 --> 11:22.957
Ah! Yes!

11:23.025 --> 11:24.892
He just posted something
from the Rainbow Grind.

11:24.961 --> 11:25.960
That was quick.

11:26.062 --> 11:28.662
Yeah, I only follow Kenny
and a squirrel.

11:28.731 --> 11:29.597
[Chuckles]

11:29.699 --> 11:31.565
Who I also suspect is Kenny.

11:31.667 --> 11:33.901
All right, let's go.

11:33.970 --> 11:35.336
This would have been the first stop

11:35.438 --> 11:38.038
on our perfect Valentine's date.

11:38.107 --> 11:41.175
I was calling it A Journey Toward Love.

11:41.277 --> 11:43.544
I would have eaten the dark.

11:43.613 --> 11:45.980
You would have eaten the milk.

11:46.082 --> 11:46.914
So us.

11:47.016 --> 11:48.616
Classic Brenny.

11:48.684 --> 11:51.552
Did his boyfriend dump him,
or did he die?

11:51.621 --> 11:55.055
I don't know, but he's eating
all of our chocolates.

11:55.157 --> 11:56.824
Not to sound insensitive,

11:56.926 --> 12:00.027
but you're ruining our date
with your sadness.

12:00.062 --> 12:02.129
I mean, if Brett has chosen
to opt out of our relationship,

12:02.198 --> 12:04.164
that's fine, but it doesn't mean
that I still can't enjoy

12:04.267 --> 12:05.366
the night that I had planned.

12:05.468 --> 12:06.867
After this, I'm going to see

12:06.936 --> 12:09.270
a special 20th anniversary
showing of "G.I. Jane,"

12:09.305 --> 12:10.738
who, now that I think of it,

12:10.806 --> 12:13.440
is another strong, independent
person who doesn't need a man.

12:13.509 --> 12:15.209
Mm! That would make a strong caption.

12:15.311 --> 12:18.324
Well, you should probably
get to your movie.

12:18.402 --> 12:20.147
I'm sure it's going to be
really crowded.

12:20.216 --> 12:21.048
You're right.

12:21.150 --> 12:23.350
And you know what, you guys...

12:23.419 --> 12:25.719
hang onto this.

12:28.024 --> 12:31.191
I'm so glad I'm not into guys.

12:31.294 --> 12:34.128
$10,900, $11,000.

12:34.163 --> 12:35.629
You totally wiped me out.

12:35.698 --> 12:39.367
Well, you got married, had three kids,
and became a flight attendant,

12:39.445 --> 12:41.535
so you kind of did the work for me.

12:41.637 --> 12:43.771
So I guess it's just down to you and me.

12:43.839 --> 12:45.639
But it's not fun with two people.

12:45.741 --> 12:47.841
Ethan, you can put your pegs in my car.

12:47.910 --> 12:49.476
That's against the rules.

12:49.578 --> 12:50.611
Then I quit.

12:50.713 --> 12:51.612
What? You can't quit.

12:51.714 --> 12:53.213
You're winning. You love winning.

12:53.282 --> 12:55.516
But if he's losing, am I really winning?

12:55.618 --> 12:57.651
[Gasps] My own daughter.

12:57.720 --> 13:00.955
Have you been corrupted
by this holiday, too?

13:01.023 --> 13:02.990
Maybe, but I don't
want to leave Ethan out.

13:03.092 --> 13:07.261
Your selfless gesture makes me feel
very validated in this relationship.

13:07.296 --> 13:09.163
I hear you say
I make you feel validated,

13:09.265 --> 13:11.298
and that makes my heart flutter
with happiness.

13:11.367 --> 13:13.398
And I hear my heart
filling with disappointment

13:13.476 --> 13:15.235
and my gut filling with bile.

13:15.338 --> 13:17.937
I'm going to Valueco.

13:18.119 --> 13:19.285
[Sighs]

13:21.177 --> 13:22.443
What was that?

13:22.545 --> 13:23.577
A drop in the bucket.

13:23.679 --> 13:25.379
You should see her on Earth Day.

13:25.448 --> 13:27.014
♪ Where's your upper hand? ♪

13:27.083 --> 13:29.049
It's hard to picture
you and Kenny as friends.

13:29.118 --> 13:30.517
You're so much fun.

13:30.586 --> 13:32.333
I know.

13:32.474 --> 13:34.326
I really bring him out of his shell.

13:34.443 --> 13:37.057
Well, I'm just glad we're finally alone.

13:37.159 --> 13:39.626
Allison, hi. Have you seen Kenny?

13:39.695 --> 13:43.130
He's, uh... He's about yea high,
gay as a tulip.

13:43.199 --> 13:46.266
I know what he looks like.
I'm his best friend.

13:46.369 --> 13:47.401
And he left.

13:47.470 --> 13:49.036
[Groans] Did he say where he was going?

13:49.105 --> 13:50.971
He said something
about seeing "G.I. Jane."

13:51.040 --> 13:53.240
Oh, God. He could be anywhere.

13:53.275 --> 13:55.976
Pretty sure he's in a movie
theater seeing "G.I. Jane."

13:56.078 --> 13:57.144
This is all my fault.

13:57.213 --> 13:59.013
If I hadn't made him my gay puppy,

13:59.115 --> 14:01.115
[sighs] none of this
would have happened.

14:01.217 --> 14:02.449
You must feel awful.

14:02.551 --> 14:04.952
I wish you could go feel awful
over there.

14:05.054 --> 14:05.919
Oh!

14:06.022 --> 14:08.088
I see. Okay.

14:08.124 --> 14:10.824
I am dedicating this Valentine's Day

14:10.926 --> 14:13.961
to finding and supporting
my sad, gay son,

14:14.063 --> 14:15.462
wherever he may be.

14:15.531 --> 14:17.865
That is the sweetest thing
I have ever heard.

14:17.933 --> 14:19.900
I wish there more men
in the world like you.

14:20.002 --> 14:20.868
Oh.

14:20.936 --> 14:22.636
I'm his son. I'm just like him.

14:22.705 --> 14:23.837
I want to kiss you.

14:23.939 --> 14:25.706
And give you a free scone.

14:26.675 --> 14:27.641
That's nice.

14:27.743 --> 14:29.777
We don't even need Kenny.

14:29.879 --> 14:32.112
We just need the idea of him.

14:32.214 --> 14:34.114
Jimmy.

14:34.183 --> 14:36.050
It's not our year.

14:36.152 --> 14:37.451
Come on.

14:39.121 --> 14:41.488
Mm, baby, you're coming home with me.

14:41.590 --> 14:43.257
[Grunts]

14:43.292 --> 14:45.759
Would you like a quesadilla?

14:45.828 --> 14:48.044
Mm! A sample that hasn't been pawed at?

14:48.142 --> 14:49.341
Yes, please.

14:49.443 --> 14:51.799
We're pushing the pepper jack
because it's about to turn.

14:51.901 --> 14:54.635
Oh, I'll risk it. [Chuckles]

14:54.737 --> 14:55.669
Quiet night, huh?

14:55.704 --> 14:57.137
Most people prefer not to spend

14:57.206 --> 14:59.873
their most romantic night
of the year in a cold warehouse.

14:59.942 --> 15:01.475
Well, they don't know
what they're missing

15:01.577 --> 15:04.011
'cause I could do this
literally forever.

15:04.113 --> 15:09.149
Rotisserie chicken is still $4.99.

15:11.253 --> 15:12.119
Ohh.

15:12.221 --> 15:13.620
It's just a coincidence.

15:15.124 --> 15:19.593
Oh, baby, you're coming home with me.
[Chuckles]

15:19.695 --> 15:21.228
Oh, my God.

15:21.330 --> 15:24.331
Is she the ghost
of my Valentine's future?

15:24.400 --> 15:25.899
Am I really Scrooge?

15:25.968 --> 15:27.601
You do kind of give off that vibe.

15:27.703 --> 15:30.137
[Sighs]

15:30.239 --> 15:33.377
<i>This is perfect.
I'd much rather be here alone.</i>

15:33.463 --> 15:35.042
<i>I get all the popcorn to myself,</i>

15:35.111 --> 15:36.150
<i>and I don't have to listen</i>

15:36.236 --> 15:38.545
<i>to Brett do that annoying thing
with his straw.</i>

15:38.647 --> 15:40.247
[Straw squeaking]

15:40.349 --> 15:43.183
Can you stop that?

15:43.285 --> 15:45.118
Oh, sorry. No. I'm not doing this.

15:45.220 --> 15:47.788
It's something my ex-boyfriend did.
Yeah, he dumped me.

15:47.890 --> 15:49.590
This was supposed to be
our Valentine's date.

15:49.692 --> 15:50.824
[Chuckles]

15:50.926 --> 15:52.893
[Squeaking continues]

15:52.995 --> 15:55.762
- It's so annoying, right?
- Yeah, it is.

15:56.999 --> 15:59.032
You know why I love this movie?

15:59.135 --> 16:02.169
Because of the wisdom
of Master Chief John Urgayle,

16:02.271 --> 16:06.039
who says, "Pain is your friend.

16:06.142 --> 16:08.408
It will keep you awake and angry!

16:08.477 --> 16:10.043
But you know the best thing about pain?

16:10.146 --> 16:12.546
It lets you know you're not dead yet!"

16:12.648 --> 16:13.647
all: Shh! Shh! Shh! Shh!

16:13.749 --> 16:15.841
Oh, please. I'm not spoiling anything.

16:15.924 --> 16:18.358
This movie's 20 years old.

16:18.554 --> 16:20.120
[Camera shutter clicking]

16:20.222 --> 16:21.755
I'm gonna have to ask you to leave.

16:21.857 --> 16:22.956
What? No, please.

16:23.025 --> 16:25.244
I have to watch this movie
in order to heal myself.

16:25.330 --> 16:27.049
Nobody kicked Liz out of Jamaica.

16:27.127 --> 16:28.252
Well, I'm kicking you out of here,

16:28.307 --> 16:29.706
unless you want to be arrested.

16:29.869 --> 16:32.332
Okay, fine. I'll leave peacefully.

16:32.434 --> 16:34.900
Okay, just so you know,
half the relationships in here

16:34.962 --> 16:36.962
are going to end,
statistically speaking.

16:37.072 --> 16:38.166
Yeah.

16:38.275 --> 16:41.283
Some probably tonight.
It's gonna be you two!

16:42.892 --> 16:45.056
I just need chocolates or cards

16:45.134 --> 16:47.734
or those hearts
with the stupid writing on them.

16:47.829 --> 16:49.696
Why is all this Easter stuff out?

16:49.731 --> 16:50.897
It's not tomorrow yet.

16:50.999 --> 16:52.832
Please don't let it be too late.

16:52.868 --> 16:54.801
It's not too late. It's not too...

16:54.903 --> 16:56.503
[Panting]

17:00.943 --> 17:01.975
Oh!

17:02.044 --> 17:04.544
Clive! What are you doing here?

17:04.646 --> 17:06.776
I listened to what you said.

17:06.854 --> 17:08.425
I thought I could get some sweet deals.

17:08.502 --> 17:11.084
I got six shrimp rings
and a paper shredder.

17:11.153 --> 17:12.452
Oh, don't listen to me.

17:12.521 --> 17:14.721
I don't know what I'm talking about.

17:14.790 --> 17:17.357
I was completely wrong
about Valentine's Day.

17:17.459 --> 17:18.858
- You were?
- Yes.

17:18.926 --> 17:21.627
It seemed fake and stupid to me

17:21.713 --> 17:24.130
because I didn't know
what people were feeling.

17:24.232 --> 17:28.001
I mean, I knew all this time
that something was missing.

17:28.069 --> 17:30.637
I thought it was warehouse shopping.

17:30.739 --> 17:34.240
But now I know what was missing was you.

17:34.309 --> 17:40.146
I feel it, Clive.
I feel the magic of the season.

17:40.248 --> 17:43.416
Clive Murray...

17:43.518 --> 17:45.118
will you be my Valentine?

17:45.220 --> 17:46.086
Yeah.

17:46.154 --> 17:48.555
It's a pack of Peeps.

17:48.624 --> 17:50.567
Hell to the yes.

17:50.592 --> 17:53.760
♪

17:53.829 --> 17:55.207
Okay, Dad, this is crazy.

17:55.278 --> 17:57.597
He wasn't at the Rainbow Grind.
He wasn't at the movies.

17:57.699 --> 17:58.698
He's not gonna be here.

17:58.800 --> 18:00.834
Hey, read his post.

18:00.902 --> 18:05.071
It's a squirrel with a Santa hat.
Dad, this means nothing.

18:05.173 --> 18:06.640
[Sighs] Jimmy, read the caption.

18:06.708 --> 18:07.874
"I'm over Valentine's Day.

18:07.943 --> 18:09.743
I wish I could go back to Christmas."

18:09.811 --> 18:12.445
Kenny and Brett met in the choir
room during Christmastime.

18:12.514 --> 18:13.647
I promise you he is here.

18:13.715 --> 18:16.116
[Piano playing]

18:16.218 --> 18:17.717
[Sighs]

18:17.819 --> 18:20.966
Hey, buddy. What are you doing?

18:21.082 --> 18:23.723
I took myself on a date
to make myself feel better,

18:23.792 --> 18:25.426
but I'm not Liz, mon.

18:25.496 --> 18:28.695
I can't just book a flight,
enjoy the touch of a local fisherman,

18:28.797 --> 18:30.163
and magically feel better.

18:30.232 --> 18:32.766
This night has made me feel
even more alone.

18:32.868 --> 18:34.167
This is my alone chord.

18:34.269 --> 18:35.635
[Minor chord plays]

18:35.737 --> 18:37.971
It's from "Music Man."

18:38.073 --> 18:39.139
[Dissonant notes play]

18:39.241 --> 18:40.306
[Sighs]

18:40.409 --> 18:42.609
Come on, little buddy.

18:42.711 --> 18:45.378
Let's get you away from this sad piano.

18:45.480 --> 18:46.546
You are so light.

18:46.648 --> 18:48.848
Thank you. I haven't been eating.

18:52.888 --> 18:54.387
[Grunts]

18:54.489 --> 18:56.790
[Clears throat]

18:56.858 --> 18:59.759
Took me 16 years
to get my first boyfriend,

18:59.828 --> 19:02.123
and I lost him in six weeks.

19:02.239 --> 19:04.497
And one of those weeks, he had strep,
so it doesn't even count.

19:04.599 --> 19:08.489
Well, hey, look, it took me 18 years
to have my first Valentine's Day,

19:08.560 --> 19:10.503
and it didn't work out so well, either.

19:10.572 --> 19:15.408
But you are gonna have many,
many more boyfriends in your life.

19:15.477 --> 19:17.711
And some will last weeks.
Some will last months.

19:17.779 --> 19:20.346
Some will last a night!

19:22.317 --> 19:23.750
I was going to say

19:23.785 --> 19:27.120
was that hopefully one
will last a lifetime.

19:27.155 --> 19:30.523
But for now you go through
as much heartache as you need.

19:30.625 --> 19:32.325
Do you mean it?

19:32.394 --> 19:34.427
Yes, of course.

19:34.529 --> 19:37.497
Look...

19:37.599 --> 19:40.734
If you want to cry or talk,

19:40.802 --> 19:43.970
even if you want to play
that song again,

19:44.072 --> 19:46.806
then you go right ahead and do it.

19:46.908 --> 19:47.741
Right, Jimmy?

19:47.843 --> 19:49.609
Yep. Yeah.

19:49.711 --> 19:53.546
We're here for you, so you... play it.

19:53.648 --> 19:54.714
Okay.

20:00.255 --> 20:02.689
You know what, I don't need it.

20:02.758 --> 20:03.823
Oh, thank God.

20:03.925 --> 20:06.927
I said it was okay. It wasn't okay.

20:07.099 --> 20:10.911
- Hey, are you sure?
- Yeah.

20:11.098 --> 20:12.685
But I am gonna Instagram you guys

20:12.786 --> 20:14.601
'cause you made my Valentine's Day.

20:14.703 --> 20:17.203
Wait, uh, is it regular feed
or squirrel feed?

20:17.305 --> 20:18.137
Oh, squirrel feed.

20:18.240 --> 20:19.639
That's where all the good stuff goes.

20:19.741 --> 20:21.908
Oh, you know, I noticed that.

20:22.010 --> 20:23.877
You guys kind of look like a couple.

20:23.979 --> 20:25.144
Yeah, a couple of studs.

20:25.247 --> 20:26.045
[Both chuckle]

20:26.147 --> 20:27.113
No, like a couple.

20:27.215 --> 20:29.015
Like, you're even wearing the same coat.

20:32.549 --> 20:35.484
- More wine?
- Of course.

20:43.394 --> 20:44.626
To Valentine's Day.

20:44.728 --> 20:49.064
You know, I get it.
This place is very peaceful.

20:49.166 --> 20:51.718
Does anybody know
where they keep the rakes?

20:52.002 --> 20:54.039
They're having a two-pack special.

20:54.132 --> 20:55.637
Please get me out of here.

20:55.706 --> 20:58.781
You're gonna have to wait 20 minutes.
I'm getting my tires changed.

